cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.NE

The paper proposes a data-driven framework that uses machine learning methods to estimate dynamic origin-destination demand using high-granular traffic data. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves statistical clustering and optimization methods, which are relevant to the social and information sciences (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the proposed framework uses a GPU-based stochastic projected gradient descent method, which is a type of neural network optimization, making it relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
